WEBVTT

00:00.040 --> 00:01.387
Previously on <i>Suits...</i>

00:01.414 --> 00:03.404
You looked me in the eye,
and told me that your hood

00:03.504 --> 00:04.769
was rock solid?

00:04.771 --> 00:06.738
You make it right on your own,
or I will.

00:06.740 --> 00:08.807
You want to settle?
Let me save you some time.

00:08.809 --> 00:10.542
We pass.
You think I don't know

00:10.544 --> 00:11.810
this was your doing?

00:11.812 --> 00:13.345
Daniel Hardman doesn't work you.
You work him.

00:13.347 --> 00:14.980
What did Hardman
find in those files?

00:14.982 --> 00:16.515
I don't know,
and I don't care.

00:16.517 --> 00:19.317
I'm entitled to name one
new senior partner a year.

00:19.319 --> 00:20.752
I'm naming you.

00:20.754 --> 00:21.853
You think he's valuing you.

00:21.855 --> 00:23.021
He's buying you.

00:23.023 --> 00:24.923
Hardman actually <i>sees</i> me!

00:24.925 --> 00:26.691
You kept me waiting five years.

00:26.693 --> 00:28.693
You can wait another 24 hours.

00:28.695 --> 00:31.396
It's your grandma.
She passed away.

00:31.398 --> 00:32.564
No.

00:32.566 --> 00:34.766
Either Jessica
will retain her position,

00:34.768 --> 00:38.503
or I will resume control
of Pearson Hardman.

00:39.666 --> 00:41.199
Well...

00:41.201 --> 00:43.968
in a few minutes, we'll know.

00:43.970 --> 00:46.398
Last time we spoke,
there was a lot of talk about

00:46.399 --> 00:48.007
peeling each other
off the walls.

00:48.090 --> 00:48.678
I just want to say--

00:48.896 --> 00:51.931
Stop talking.

00:51.933 --> 00:54.867
As you wish.

00:56.000 --> 01:02.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:18.659 --> 01:19.858
What are you doing here?

01:19.860 --> 01:21.393
Rachel, meet the file room.

01:21.395 --> 01:23.495
It's where we store information

01:23.497 --> 01:24.563
on the cases
that we're working on.

01:24.565 --> 01:26.932
No, I-I just mean,

01:26.934 --> 01:29.735
I don't believe that Harvey
would make you come and work

01:29.737 --> 01:33.405
the day after...

01:33.407 --> 01:36.575
You can say it.

01:37.812 --> 01:39.945
Okay, I'll say it.

01:39.947 --> 01:41.747
The day after
my grandmother died.

01:41.749 --> 01:43.215
And Harvey doesn't know.

01:43.217 --> 01:44.750
What? Why?

01:44.752 --> 01:46.251
'Cause,
there's a vote going on,

01:46.253 --> 01:47.886
and he's got bigger things
on his mind.

01:47.888 --> 01:50.255
- Mike, he'd want to know.
- Oh, really, you know that?

01:50.257 --> 01:52.324
You and--you and Harvey
are best friends now?

01:52.326 --> 01:54.793
Okay, then tell Donna.
Just tell somebody that--

01:54.795 --> 01:56.261
I don't want people to know.

01:56.263 --> 01:58.630
If you tell people,
they will understand,

01:58.632 --> 02:01.100
and then you can go home,
and you can really deal with--

02:01.102 --> 02:04.903
Deal with what, Rachel?

02:04.905 --> 02:06.271
The fact that I missed
my last-ever chance

02:06.273 --> 02:08.273
to see my grandmother
because I was too busy at work?

02:08.275 --> 02:09.741
Oh, come on,
that's not fair.

02:09.744 --> 02:11.276
You were an amazing grandson.

02:11.278 --> 02:12.644
You--you were buying
her an apartment--

02:12.646 --> 02:14.480
I bought her an apartment
because I felt guilty

02:14.482 --> 02:16.015
for not having seen her
for two months.

02:16.017 --> 02:17.549
No, you were buying
her an apartment because--

02:17.551 --> 02:19.651
This is not a debate, Rachel.

02:19.653 --> 02:22.254
All right, I came to work
because I want to work.

02:22.256 --> 02:24.456
I'm not telling people because
I don't want to talk about it.

02:24.458 --> 02:26.525
And now I'm gonna go out
and get some fresh air,

02:26.527 --> 02:27.793
and when I get back,

02:27.795 --> 02:31.096
I really hope
you will be done bothering me.

02:42.108 --> 02:43.675
The managing partner...

02:43.677 --> 02:44.810
is Daniel Hardman.

02:44.812 --> 02:47.079
Effective immediately.

02:50.985 --> 02:52.217
I want to thank you for

02:52.219 --> 02:53.452
trusting me with
the future of this firm.

02:53.454 --> 02:55.788
I won't let you down.

02:55.790 --> 02:57.956
Let's get back to work.

02:57.958 --> 02:58.957
Harvey...

02:58.959 --> 03:01.060
a word.

03:01.062 --> 03:04.063
I know that we have
a rocky history,

03:04.065 --> 03:06.465
but I would be
a fool not to recognize

03:06.467 --> 03:08.467
your value to this firm.
Daniel, you won.

03:08.469 --> 03:10.402
You don't need
to blow smoke up my ass.

03:10.404 --> 03:12.237
I'm not blowing smoke.

03:12.239 --> 03:13.839
I told you this
from the day I came back,

03:13.841 --> 03:16.208
that I was us to find
a way to work together.

03:16.210 --> 03:18.077
Why say this to me
and not Jessica?

03:18.079 --> 03:19.578
I will.

03:19.580 --> 03:21.180
But her name is on the door.

03:21.182 --> 03:22.681
She's not going anywhere.

03:22.683 --> 03:27.586
I want to make sure that you're
not going anywhere either.

03:27.588 --> 03:29.421
It's time to go.

03:29.423 --> 03:31.623
I can name 12 partners
who will follow you anywhere.

03:31.625 --> 03:34.093
We can have every associate
in the place.

03:34.095 --> 03:35.527
Harvey...

03:35.529 --> 03:37.229
we're not going anywhere.

03:37.231 --> 03:39.264
We have a non-compete clause.

03:39.266 --> 03:42.701
We quit, we can't practice law
in New York for a year.

03:42.703 --> 03:44.002
Contracts
were made to be broken.

03:44.004 --> 03:46.171
Not when
they're written by me.

03:46.173 --> 03:48.440
Well, maybe we should take
a year off.

03:48.442 --> 03:50.109
- How would that go?
- You could teach.

03:50.111 --> 03:52.377
- I could also kill myself.
- You could write a book.

03:52.379 --> 03:54.012
- Next.
- What about travel?

03:54.014 --> 03:55.380
You have the means.

03:55.382 --> 03:56.515
See the world.

03:56.517 --> 03:58.317
Teaching, writing, traveling.

03:58.319 --> 04:00.085
You know what
you're talking about?

04:00.087 --> 04:01.120
Running.

04:01.122 --> 04:02.354
I'm not running.

04:02.356 --> 04:05.190
We can't stay here.
Not working for him.

04:05.192 --> 04:06.625
Yes, we can.

04:06.627 --> 04:08.327
We are going
to swallow our pride,

04:08.329 --> 04:09.661
and we're going to wait

04:09.663 --> 04:12.297
until we can make a move
from a position of strength.

04:12.299 --> 04:13.732
That's your tactic?

04:13.734 --> 04:15.567
Holding your head down
and waiting?

04:15.569 --> 04:16.935
That's what he did.

04:16.937 --> 04:18.670
It took him five years.
Do you really think it's gonna

04:18.672 --> 04:21.072
take him five years
to screw up again?

04:21.075 --> 04:22.941
I bet it'll be more
like five minutes.

04:22.943 --> 04:25.410
- Jessica--
- That's enough.

04:25.412 --> 04:27.846
This happened today.
Today.

04:27.848 --> 04:30.048
We just took the hit.

04:30.050 --> 04:31.450
We suffered a loss,

04:31.452 --> 04:33.685
and you don't make
major life decisions

04:33.687 --> 04:36.321
when you're reeling
from a loss.

04:42.929 --> 04:45.831
I wanna buy some weed.

04:47.067 --> 04:49.535
Sorry, man, you got
it wrong, but, uh,

04:49.537 --> 04:50.569
hey, if you want a paper,
I'll be--

04:50.571 --> 04:52.804
I'm not a cop, okay?

04:52.806 --> 04:54.006
I know for a fact
that you're a dealer.

04:54.008 --> 04:55.307
I've seen you here
every single day.

04:55.309 --> 04:56.875
I know the drill.

04:56.877 --> 04:58.477
A guy comes up,
he hands you a $100 bill,

04:58.479 --> 05:00.546
he walks away with a folded
newspaper full of weed.

05:00.548 --> 05:01.847
Well, I have money.

05:01.849 --> 05:03.382
If you don't want it,
I'll be happy to take it

05:03.384 --> 05:05.250
to the coffee cart
down at 50th and Lex

05:05.252 --> 05:09.021
who we both know
is your competition.

05:13.426 --> 05:14.626
Have a great day.

05:14.628 --> 05:16.261
Yeah.

05:16.263 --> 05:19.431
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

05:19.433 --> 05:22.968
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

05:22.970 --> 05:26.605
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

05:26.607 --> 05:30.175
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

05:30.177 --> 05:33.145
♪ living in a beehive
of your mind ♪

05:33.147 --> 05:36.748
♪ me and missus so busy,
busy making money ♪

05:36.750 --> 05:38.850
♪ all right

05:38.852 --> 05:44.156
♪ all that time
imagine this ♪

05:44.158 --> 05:45.534
♪ the greenback boogie

05:45.535 --> 05:48.135
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Suits 2x10 ♪</font>
